{
  "doc_id": "26051",
  "text": "Seeds were germinated on moistened filter paper in a growth cabinet (22 o C -20 o C, 16 h light) for approximately two weeks. DNA was extracted from leaf tissue of 8-12 individuals using a CTAB-based method [CITATION_1] . For samples collected from field trials, DNA was extracted from a leaf sample from a single individual, using the previously described method. Genotyping was done using eight simple sequence repeat (SSR) markers -G03_020, G05_033, G07_037, G01_053, G07_065, G05_071, G05_088, and G05_099 [CITATION_2] . Each forward primer was labelled with a different fluorophore (6-FAM, HEX or TMR) to facilitate visualisation using capillary electrophoresis. The PCRs were carried out in a 10 µl solution containing 2 µL Hot FirePol Blend MasterMix with 10mM MgCl 2 (Soltis BioDyne, Tartu, Estonia), 0.5 µl each primer (8 µM), and 2 µl DNA solution. The PCR cycling conditions were: 95°C for 15 minutes, 40 cycles of 95°C for 20 seconds, 58°C for 30 seconds, 72°C for 45 seconds, and 72°C for 5 minutes. The PCR products were size separated on an ABI 3130xl Genetic Analyzer and genotyped using GeneMapper 4.0 (Applied Biosystems). Genetic diversity parameters were calculated using GenAlEx 6.0 [CITATION_3] . Genetic distances and bootstrapping were done using the MSA software package [CITATION_4] . Genetic distances were calculated using the proportion of shared alleles, Nei's chord distance, and Cavalli-Sforza and Edwards chord distance with 1000 bootstrap repetitions. Neighbourjoining trees and consensus trees were constructed using the 'Neighbour' and 'Consense' programmes in PHYLIP.",
